content.description:
EVEN A ROTTWEILER CAN BARK 5.10a ** (160') M (2b)

In the middle of the main face (right of the obvious diagonal crack), begin with the right side of the "V" and climb good flakes and cracks to the top.
content.protection: Mixed, 2 bolts with a range of small to medium cams needed in the cracks as well as for the gear belay on top.
content.location:
Climbs the middle of the face (right side of the "V")

Single rope rappel from the chain anchors down and (climbers) left/east from the top.

content.description:
EVEN A POODLE CAN BITE 5.9+ * (160') G

Excellent (dirty) cracks lead up the corner on the right to exit by the small fir tree on top
content.location: at right end of the canine Cliff

climbs.name: EVEN A DOG CAN SHAKE HANDS

content.description:
EVEN A DOG CAN SHAKE HANDS 5.9 * (160') M (3b)

Takes the left side of th e"V" to join the main diagonal crack on the face. Follow this left through the brush (!) till you reach the finger crack. Traverse right and up to the top.
content.protection: Mixed - 3 bolts and a range of nuts
content.location: at the left side of the face
